AttributeList.Text:
========================================================================== = F C 1 0 - C T R L O B J C T = ==========================================================================
Date : 13.04.99 Ver. : 0.4 Init : NAK, JoM
Ver. 0.2 - include : Bit to activate alarm flash lamp : feedback type 4 : motor with avalibile and set feedback Ver. 0.3 - Include : output blocked - After motor fault (only norferm project)
Ver. 0.4 - Exclude Ver. 0.3, feedback type 4 : motor with avalibile and set feedback and monitor control.
Flag uses in function M 4.0 - 1HZ onshot trigger bit (uses to count in seconds)
M 6.0 - set if new feedback alarm (used to activate alarm flash lamp)
Data words uses in function
DB10, dw X - command word from SCADA Bit 0 = auto Bit 1 = Manuel deactivate Bit 2 = Manuel activate Bit 3 = spare Bit 4 = spare Bit 5 = spare Bit 6 = spare
DB11, dw X - info word to SCADA Bit 0 = activated Bit 1 = changing Bit 2 = faulty Bit 3 = auto_man, Manuel = 1 Bit 4 = man_on_off Bit 5 = spare Bit 6 = spare Bit 7 = spare Bit 8 = spare Bit 9 = spare Bit 10 = spare Bit 11 = spare Bit 12 = spare Bit 13 = spare Bit 14 = fb_error - Alarm feedback error Bit 15 = spare
DB13 byte x & byte x+1 - Timer work area Byte x = spare Byte x+1 = fb_timer - Feedback timer item
DB 14, bit 0 - 7 & byte X+1 - Intern status & communication to monitor functions Bit 0 = spare Bit 1 = spare Bit 2 = spare Bit 3 = process_req - Process request from functions Bit 4 = process_mirror1 - Mirror process request Bit 5 = spare Bit 6 = spare Bit 7 = spare
Byte x+1 alarm_reset_timer alarm bit reset time Bit 0-3 spare Bit 4-7 alarm reset timer for feedback error

LineComment.Text: if commamd bits = 0 then no commands
Show Reset FB in "Item Info & Operation" popup
Show Set FB in "Item Info & Operation" popup
If new monitor alarm set alarm flash lamp
Wait 5 seconds to reset alarm bits
Larst 4 bits time reset monitor/process alarm
Count 1 second down, in larst 4 bit time reset F.B. alarm
